# Files autoformat and autolint should skip.
#
# Each non-comment non-blank line is a bash glob pattern (supports
# `*`, `?`, `[...]`; no `**`, no negations) matched against the file
# path passed to autoformat/autolint. A match → the script exits 0
# without running any tool.
#
# This file is read by both autoformat and autolint — autoformat's
# AUTOFORMAT_DIR and autolint's AUTOLINT_DIR both default to
# ~/.config/autoformat/, so one file covers both.

# karabiner-elements owns this file — reformatting it means the app
# will just rewrite on next save, producing churn and noise diffs.
*/karabiner.json

# Generated by `mise lock`; contains per-platform checksums + URLs in
# a specific order. Running taplo over it re-emits differently and
# would churn on every lockfile refresh.
*/mise.lock

# iTerm2 dynamic-profile file — iTerm reads this to configure the
# terminal. Reformatting could change key order in ways iTerm
# doesn't like.
*/iterm2-dotfiles-dyn-profile.json
